IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THROUGH ELECTRONIC REUSE, PCS FOR PEOPLE PROVIDES THE OPPORTUNITY FOR ALL INDIVIDUALS, FAMILIES, AND NONPROFITS WITH LOW INCOME TO BENEFIT FROM THE LIFE-CHANGING IMPACT OF COMPUTERS, INTERNET, AND DIGITAL SKILLS. IN FY 2021-22, PCS FOR PEOPLE DISTRIBUTED MORE THAN 54,000 COMPUTERS TO THOSE IN NEED.
IRS990.MissionDesc: FOUNDED IN 1998, PCS FOR PEOPLE WAS CREATED TO PROVIDE THE OPPORTUNITY FOR LOW-INCOME INDIVIDUALS AND NONPROFITS TO BENEFIT FROM THE LIFE CHANGING IMPACT OF COMPUTERS, MOBILE INTERNET, AND DIGITAL LITERACY.
IRS990.Desc: SOURCE, REFURBISH, DISTRIBUTE, AND SUPPORTSOURCE: OUR ABILITY TO DISTRIBUTE AFFORDABLE TECHNOLOGY IS DEPENDENT ON OUR RECYCLING PARTNERSHIPS. WE OFFER A NATION-WIDE FREE END-OF-LIFE IT SERVICE OFFERING THAT INCLUDES NAID AAA-CERTIFIED DATA SANITIZATION AND R2-CERTIFIED SUSTAINABLE ELECTRONICS RECYCLING. REFURBISH: THE DONATED TECHNOLOGY IS SECURELY PROCESSED IN OUR WAREHOUSES. COMPUTERS AND THEN ARE CLEANED, PROCESSED THROUGH A STRINGENT QUALITY CHECK, AND INSTALLED WITH A NEW OPERATING SYSTEM. DISTRIBUTE: AFFORDABLE HIGH-QUALITY COMPUTERS ARE DISTRIBUTED TO INCOME QUALIFIED INDIVIDUALS THROUGH OUR RETAIL STORES, ONLINE, AND THROUGH NATIONAL DISTRIBUTION EVENTS. CONTINUED ON SCHEDULE O. SUPPORT: ONCE A CUSTOMER HAS RECEIVED A COMPUTER, IT IS IMPORTANT THAT THEY ARE CONFIDENT IN THEIR PURCHASE AND FEEL SUPPORTED. EACH COMPUTER COMES WITH A 1-YEAR HARDWARE WARRANTY, FREE DIGITAL LITERACY TRAINING, AND PHONE SUPPORT. IN FY 2021-22, PCS FOR PEOPLE COLLECTED OVER 71,000 COMPUTERS AND LAPTOPS. MORE THAN 54,000 OF THESE COMPUTERS WERE REFURBISHED AND DISTRIBUTED TO LOW-INCOME FAMILIES AND INDIVIDUALS. PCS FOR PEOPLE ALSO SUPPORTED THE COMPUTERS DISTRIBUTED WITH WARRANTY REPAIRS AND OFFERED DISCOUNTED REPAIRS AFTER THE WARRANTY PERIOD. REPAIRS WERE $25 AND ANY PARTS NEEDED WERE FREE. IN FY 2021-22, OVER 2,400 REPAIRS WERE COMPLETED AT AN AVERAGE COST OF $16 PER REPAIR.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: MOBILE INTERNET SERVICEPCS FOR PEOPLE OFFERS NATIONWIDE LOW-COST HIGH SPEED 4G LTE MOBILE INTERNET SERVICE PROVIDED BY MOBILE BEACON AND MOBILE CITIZEN. PLANS ARE PREPAID WITH NO CREDIT CHECK OR HIDDEN FEES FOR INCOME ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUALS. IN FY 2021-22, PCS FOR PEOPLE OFFERED LOW-COST HIGH SPEED 4G LTE INTERNET TO MORE THAN 113,000 ELIGIBLE HOUSEHOLDS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: PCS FOR PEOPLE OFFERS IN-HOUSE, LOW-COST HIGH SPEED FIXED INTERNET SERVICE IN 9 STATES. SERVICE IS FIXED AT $15 A MONTH AND HOUSEHOLDS WHO ARE INCOME ELIGIBLE TO ENROLL IN THE AFFORDABILITY CONNECTIVITY PROGRAM (ACP) CAN HAVE THIS FEE COVERED. IN FY 2021-22, PCS FOR PEOPLE'S FIXED INTERNET SERVICE CONSISTS OF NEARLY 45 NETWORK TOWERS AND 15 MULTI-DWELLING UNITS (MDUS) COVERING MORE THAN 20,000 HOUSEHOLDS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PCS FOR PEOPLE HAS A THOROUGH PROCESS TO REVIEW FORM 990 AND ALL REQUIRED SCHEDULES. A FIRST DRAFT OF THE DOCUMENT IS PROVIDED TO ALL KEY EMPLOYEES FOR REVIEW AND COMMENT. THE FINAL DRAFT IS PROVIDED TO ALL BOARD MEMBERS FOR THEIR REVIEW.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PCS FOR PEOPLE CONSISTENTLY MONITORS AND ENFORCES ITS CONFLICT-OF-INTEREST POLICY. ALL DIRECTORS AND OFFICERS ARE REQUIRED TO DISCLOSE ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST. TO ENSURE COMPLIANCE, ALL BUSINESS TRANSACTIONS ARE ANALYZED TO ENSURE THAT NO CONFLICT OF INTEREST IS PRESENT. IF A CONFLICT IS DETERMINED TO EXIST, THE BOARD WILL DETERMINE WHETHER PCS FOR PEOPLE CAN OBTAIN, WITH REASONABLE EFFORTS, A MORE ADVANTAGEOUS TRANSACTION THAT WOULD NOT GIVE RISE TO A CONFLICT. IF A MORE ADVANTAGEOUS TRANSACTION IS NOT REASONABLY AVAILABLE, THE BOARD WILL DETERMINE, BY A MAJORITY OF DISINTERESTED MEMBERS, WHETHER THE TRANSACTION IS IN PCS FOR PEOPLE'S BEST INTEREST AND IS FAIR AND REASONABLE. DECISIONS RELATED TO TRANSACTIONS INVOLVING ACTUAL OR POSSIBLE CONFLICTS OF INTEREST ARE DOCUMENTED.
